# Modes of Operation

The editor has three current modes (Readonly, Unfocused, Focus) with planned future modes (Theme Mode, Mermaid Mode). All mode logic lives in `live-wysiwyg-integration.js`.

## Mode Transition Triggers

| Transition | Trigger |
|---|---|
| Readonly to Unfocused | Edit button (accesskey e) or period (`.`) shortcut |
| Unfocused to Focus | Focus Mode toolbar button or browser fullscreen |
| Focus to Unfocused | X button or Escape key |
| Unfocused to Readonly | Cancel button |

## Cursor Preservation Across Transitions

Every mode transition that affects the editing surface must preserve cursor position and text selection. Do not add transitions that lose the cursor without explicit user intent (e.g., Cancel).

- **Readonly to Unfocused**: `storeSelectionIfReadMode` captures; `readonly_to_edit_mode_text_selection` applies.
- **Unfocused to Focus / Focus to Unfocused**: `_captureEditorSelection` before reparenting; `_restoreEditorSelection` after.

## Future Modes

Theme Mode and Mermaid Mode (documented in `DESIGN-modes-of-operation.md`) must follow the same lifecycle pattern:

1. Explicit entry and exit triggers
2. Cursor/state preservation where applicable
3. Cleanup on exit (overlays, listeners, injected styles)
